subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Jennifer Rosales and Dorothy Delasin of the Philippines shot a seven-under-par 65 Sunday to beat South Korea by two strokes at the Women’s World Cup of Golf in Sun City, South Africa.Ji-Yai Shin and Eun-Hee Ji of South Korea were comfortably in the lead after nine holes, but Rosales and Delasin had five birdies and finished at 18-under 198 at Gary Player Country Club.Juli Inkster and Pat Hurst of the United States tied for 10th.
